description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity for someone with proven programme support management experience and organisational skills to join North Bristol NHS Trust to contribute to the development of the One NBT Digital Vision. The post holder will support the Electronic Patient Record Programme Manager and Clinical Leads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role requiring exceptional organisational, information management, project management, planning and communication skills. You will need to demonstrate the following skills;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;analytical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;organisational&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;administrative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to know and understand the theory of project management and be able to support the process where the project manager will be using it every day to manage the project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has a flexible approach and is able to work with the minimum of supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will be working alongside an extremely busy and supportive Digital Informatics Programme team and will be focused on large Digital Clinical Transformation programmes which span across the organisation and the wider System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The clue is in the title – Project Support – and support in whatever shape it takes is something that really makes the Project Support role indispensable. The nature of the role means you are often the centre point for the project. The project manager relies heavily on you to make things go smoothly. If meetings need arranging, agendas set and actions chased, it’s the Project Support Officer that makes it happen. The same applies with travel arrangements, team events, last-minute project purchases and getting the suppliers time in the diary. You remove any blockers!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s these little ‘support’ requirements that appear on every project at any one time that need a good project support manager so the project manager can delegate. And every project manager wants a right hand person that can provide support when it’s needed the m&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vacancy is 12 months fixed term with a potential to be extended in line with the requirements of the Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Got a question about the role? Please email:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;harriet.soderberg@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHarriet SoderbergJob titleSenior Informatics Project ManagerEmail addressharriet.soderberg@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
